criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients of both sexes;

          -  Age between 40 and 70 years;

          -  Body mass index (BMI) ≥ 30 kg/m² and <40 kg/m².

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Systolic blood pressure ≥ 160 and/or diastolic blood pressure ≥ 100 mmHg;

          -  Diabetes mellitus; Hormone replacement therapy;

          -  Evidence of secondary hypertension;

          -  Clinically evident changes in thyroid function;

          -  Acute or chronic kidney or liver disease;

          -  History of cancer in the last 5 years;

          -  Clinically evident coronary disease with a history of acute myocardial infarction
             and/or myocardial revascularization, clinical signs of heart failure, cardiac
             arrhythmia or clinically significant valve disease;

          -  Previous stroke;
